        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I get this error: \"'Zend_Db_Table_Exception' with message 'No adapter found for...\", unless I add this: Zend_Db_Table_Abstract::setDefaultAdapter($db) to the _intiDb function in the Bootsrap.\r\n\r\nI have this in application.ini:\r\n\r\nresources.db.adapter = \"pdo_mysql\"\r\nresources.db.params.dbname = \"dbname\"\r\nresources.db.params.host = \"localhost\"\r\nresources.db.params.username = \"un\"\r\nresources.db.params.password = \"111\"\r\nresources.db.isDefaultTableAdapter = true\r\n\r\nI have this code in the Bootstrap:\r\n\r\nprotected function _initDb() {\r\n\tif ($this->hasPluginResource(\"db\")) {\r\n         $dbResource = $this->getPluginResource(\"db\");\r\n\t $db = $dbResource->getDbAdapter();\r\n         Zend_Registry::set(\"db\", $db);\r\n\t}\r\n}"
        },
