        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39374",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is normal behavior you must set the default adapter.\r\n\r\nThere is no need of  Bootstrap:>_initDb(), already you are using the call through pluginResources.\r\n\r\n{quote}\r\nresources.db.adapter = \"pdo_mysql\"\r\nresources.db.params.dbname = \"dbname\"\r\nresources.db.params.host = \"localhost\"\r\nresources.db.params.username = \"un\"\r\nresources.db.params.password = \"111\"\r\nresources.db.isDefaultTableAdapter = true\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nPer default Zend_Application_Resource_Db::$_isDefaultTableAdapter = true\r\n\r\nThere is no need of:\r\n*resources.db.isDefaultTableAdapter = true*",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-18T18:49:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-18T18:49:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39377",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dyudko44",
                        "name": "dyudko44",
                        "displayName": "David Yudkowitz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If I do not need the _initDb function call then I do not fully understand then what would be the proper way to retrieve a variable that represents my database connection to use throughout the application. When I remove that function from the Bootstrap I get the error message: 'Zend_Db_Table_Exception' with message 'No adapter found for ...' \r\n\r\nThanks.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dyudko44",
                        "name": "dyudko44",
                        "displayName": "David Yudkowitz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-18T23:53:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-18T23:53:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39383",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@David \r\nThrough the key *resources*, you can configure the pluginResources that are present in Zend_Application_Resource_*\r\n\r\nconfig locale:\r\n{code}\r\nresources.locale.default = 'de_AT' see Zend_Application_Resource_Locale \r\n{code}\r\n\r\nExample of use resources.db see Zend_Application_Resource_Db\r\n{code}\r\n<?php\r\nset_include_path('\/path\/');\r\n$options = array(\r\n\t'resources' => array(\r\n        'db' => array(\r\n            'adapter' => 'pdo_mysql',\r\n           \t'params'  => array(\r\n                'dbname'   => 'dbname',\r\n                'host'     => 'host',\r\n                'username' => 'user',\r\n                'password' => 'pass'\r\n            )\r\n        )\r\n    )\r\n);\r\nrequire 'Zend\/Application.php';\r\n$application = new Zend_Application('testing', $options);\r\n$application->bootstrap(); \/\/ execute all resources\r\nvar_dump(Zend_Db_Table::getDefaultAdapter()); \r\n{code}\r\n\r\nIf the error persists, post your code so I try to simulate the error.\r\n\r\nThanks.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-19T03:56:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-19T03:56:02.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
